  "prompt": "How can a person fix their Beats headphones if one side does not work?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to troubleshoot Beats headphones when one side isn't working:\n\n1. Basic Checks\n- Ensure the audio cable is fully plugged in\n- Check Bluetooth connection is stable\n- Test with different devices to rule out source issue\n- Verify volume is balanced on both sides\n\n2. Wired Headphones\n- Examine the audio cable for damage\n- Try using a different audio cable\n- Clean the headphone jack\n- Check for loose wire connections\n\n3. Wireless Beats\n- Reset Bluetooth connection\n- Turn off/on headphones\n- Fully charge the battery\n- Forget and re-pair with device\n\n4. Advanced Troubleshooting\n- Check sound settings on your device\n- Update firmware if possible\n- Inspect internal wiring\n- Test individual speaker\n\n5. Professional Repair Options\n- Contact Beats/Apple support\n- Visit an authorized repair center\n- Consider warranty service\n- Send for professional repair\n\n6. Last Resort\n- If out of warranty, consider replacement\n- Cost of repair might exceed new headphones\n\nNote: Some repairs might require technical expertise, so professional help is recommended for complex issues.",
